      "message": "I don\u0027t think this is right. This means that the omitted-comma form isn\u0027t stable - as soon as anyone runs `cue fmt` _without_ `--simplify`, the commas come back. In general ISTM that `--simplify` should only introduce simplifications to the syntax that stay around when running `cue format` afterwards.\n\nPersonally I think that we should probably omit commas on list elements exactly as we omit commas in any other situation (i.e. always), but if we feel that will be too disruptive a change, then I\u0027d suggest omitting all commas if any comma is already omitted within a given list literal.",
